    "narrative": "For LawDog today, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (76.05) stands out as our primary engine. Facing Cameron, who carries a shaky 4.33 xERA, **Ram\u00edrez** benefits from a potent combination of elite base projections and a favorable platoon look, cementing his status as the highest-ceiling play on the roster. Similarly, **Jonathan Aranda** (68.94) is an excellent start against Assad; the 19% SP skill boost and platoon advantage offset the park factor, making him a high-efficiency utility-style anchor. **Yainer Diaz** (66.01) is also an intriguing play, as he draws a +14% park boost at Coors-adjacent levels of hitter-friendly environments, effectively masking his lower spot in the batting order.\n\nWhile our core is locked, the decision to bench **Gavin Sheets** (42.56) was the most difficult pivot. **Sheets** received a +5% bump for favorable winds, but the matchup against Skenes\u2014an elite arm with a 3.10 xERA\u2014effectively nullified his power potential, dropping him below the efficiency floor. We are opting to prioritize the higher-upside platoon edges provided by **Lawrence Butler** (62.57) and **Will Smith** (58.13), who remain the preferred options despite the latter facing the formidable Gausman. We must keep a close watch on **Daulton Varsho** (51.83); while he offers crucial speed, he faces a significant hurdle against Yamamoto. Given our obsession with SB as the league's scarcest category, we are tolerating the reduced efficiency for **Varsho** and **Jeremiah Jackson** (55.67) specifically to hunt steals, provided they don't fall further against these specific high-velocity pitchers. \n\nBeyond those pivots, we are monitoring the risks associated with the Eovaldi matchup. Both **Cal Raleigh** (46.77) and **Brendan Donovan** (51.17) are navigating difficult conditions, as Eovaldi\u2019s 3.17 xERA mandates a conservative outlook on their run-production ceilings. We are also keeping **Tyler Freeman**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve; should late-scratch reports emerge or weather patterns shift, we have the flexibility to swap in depth to preserve our game caps. With **Bryson Stott** confirmed out of the lineup today, our bench remains strictly observational to ensure we maximize our daily efficiency scores across the 5x5 categories.",
